// =============================================
//  controllers/ — Business Logic Directory
// =============================================
//  Controllers handle the "what happens" when an API
//  endpoint is hit.  They:
//    1. Receive the request (req) from a route
//    2. Interact with Models to read/write data
//    3. Send back the response (res)
//
//  Examples you'll create later:
//    • user.controller.js  → register, getProfile
//    • room.controller.js  → createRoom, joinRoom
//
//  Convention: camelCase filenames (e.g., user.controller.js)
// =============================================
